## Introduction to Command-Line in RStudio

### Definitions

*Console* expects commands in R

*Terminal* expects unix commands

*pwd* "print working directly"

*ls* shows what is present in our current directory

*ls -1* prints in long format

*ls -lr* -r flag (reverse sort)

*ls -l /usr* this passes through a different directory /usr

### Creating a directory

```{base}
cd 
mkdir command_line 
ls
```

### Working in a new directory

```{base}
cd command_line
pwd
```

*cat* file.name allows us to look at files *head* -X allows us to view the X nb of lines from the file.name

*grep* (globally search a regular expression and print) finds line matching specific strings in files

### Functions and flags

```{base}
#Finding fasta header
grep '^>' test.fasta

#Find specific amino acid sequence
grep KDRNKKNSAK test.fasta # this will flag/highlight the sequence we are looking for

#Viewing flags
man grep # shows command manual

```

flags are basically command shortcuts

```{base}
#This is using the shortcut/flag -n withing the function grep to find the chunk with the sequence: KDRNKKNSAK inside the file: test.fasta and tells us that there are 3 lines with the desired sequences
grep -n KDRNKKNSAK test.fasta
```

Tip: Remember to check where you are before running commands!!!!
